Heal zones.

A heal zone is a rectangular area that changes the player's health over time while they stand inside it. Despite the name it works in both directions: set to restore, it's a healing pool, a campfire, a regeneration field; set to drain, it's poison gas, a pool of acid, a cursed floor that bleeds the life out of anyone who lingers. The mode you choose decides which.

How a heal zone works.

While the player is inside the zone, it acts on a repeating beat. Every healing time, it applies its healing amount:

In increasing mode it adds that amount to the player's health and stamina, topping them up the longer the player stays.
In decreasing mode it subtracts that amount from health and stamina, wearing the player down for as long as they linger — a damage-over-time trap that the player has to leave or die in.

If the player's shield is raised, the change is applied to the shield's strength instead of their health and stamina, so a shield soaks a draining zone (and a healing zone tops the shield back up). A heal zone has no effect while the player is riding a vehicle. Stepping into the zone plays its entry cue — a heal sound for an increasing zone, a take sound for a decreasing one.

Heal zone fields.

The heal zone form takes the following:

Coordinates. A minimum and maximum x and y (and a minimum and maximum z on 3d maps), marking the rectangular area.

Healing amount. How much health (or shield) is added or removed on each beat.

Healing time. Milliseconds between beats, so a smaller number acts faster.

Healing mode. Increasing to restore the player, or decreasing to drain them.

Heal sound (a folder name from the heal sounds list, or none). The audio theme; the bundle supplies a heal clip (played on entry to an increasing zone) and a take clip (played on entry to a decreasing zone). Pick none for a silent zone.

Auditioning sounds in the builder.

While the heal sound list is focused in the form, press space to hear the heal clip of the highlighted theme and hold control and press L to hear its take clip.

Authoring heal zones by hand.

If you edit main.sif directly, a heal zone is: heal_zone minx maxx miny maxy mode amount time healtype. On 3d maps a minimum and maximum z follow the y pair: heal_zone minx maxx miny maxy minz maxz mode amount time healtype. Mode is written as a number — zero for decreasing, one for increasing. The healing amount and time are whole numbers, and the heal sound must match a heal sounds folder name or the word none.
